<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>{{ title }}</title>
<style>
  :root {
    --bg: #fafaf7; --fg: #1d1d1f; --muted: #6e6e73; --line: #e0e0d8;
    --accent: #0a7d57; --warn: #b94b00; --danger: #c81e1e; --gold: #b08400;
    --card: #ffffff; --code-bg: #f4f4ef;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  body { font: 15.5px/1.55 -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Helvetica Neue", sans-serif; margin: 0; background: var(--bg); color: var(--fg); }
  .wrap { max-width: 920px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 32px 24px 80px; }
  header { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); padding-bottom: 18px; margin-bottom: 28px; }
  h1 { font-size: 28px; margin: 0 0 8px; letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
  h2 { font-size: 21px; margin: 36px 0 14px; padding-top: 14px; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); }
  h3 { font-size: 17px; margin: 22px 0 10px; }
  h2:first-of-type { border-top: none; padding-top: 0; }
  .meta { color: var(--muted); font-size: 13.5px; }
  .tldr { background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 10px; padding: 18px 20px; margin: 20px 0 8px; }
  .tldr h2 { margin: 0 0 10px; border: 0; padding: 0; font-size: 18px; color: var(--accent); }
  .big-num { font-size: 26px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--accent); }
  table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; margin: 12px 0 6px; background: var(--card); font-size: 14.5px; }
  th, td { padding: 9px 11px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); text-align: left; vertical-align: top; }
  th { background: #f4f4ee; font-weight: 600; }
  td.num { text-align: right; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; white-space: nowrap; }
  th.num { text-align: right; }
  tr.winner td { background: #f1faf5; font-weight: 600; }
  tr.silver td { background: #f7f7f1; }
  tr.danger td { background: #fdf0f0; }
  tr.baseline td { color: var(--muted); font-style: italic; }
  .pill { display: inline-block; padding: 1px 7px; border-radius: 10px; font-size: 11.5px; font-weight: 600; margin-left: 4px; }
  .pill.win { background: #d9efe1; color: #0a5f3f; }
  .pill.warn { background: #f8e5c6; color: #7a4e00; }
  .pill.danger { background: #f9dcdc; color: #8a1414; }
  .pill.muted { background: #e7e7df; color: #555; }
  blockquote { border-left: 3px solid var(--accent); margin: 14px 0; padding: 4px 14px; color: #2c2c2e; background: #f0f7f3; }
  blockquote.warn { border-color: var(--warn); background: #fcf3e7; }
  code, pre { font: 13px/1.5 "SF Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace; }
  code { background: var(--code-bg); padding: 1px 5px; border-radius: 3px; }
  details { background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 8px; padding: 10px 14px; margin: 10px 0; }
  details summary { cursor: pointer; font-weight: 600; }
  ul, ol { padding-left: 22px; }
  li { margin: 4px 0; }
  .key-finding { background: #fffbe7; border: 1px solid #ecd97a; border-radius: 8px; padding: 12px 16px; margin: 14px 0; }
  footer { color: var(--muted); font-size: 13px; margin-top: 40px; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); padding-top: 14px; }
  .staleness { padding: 8px 12px; border-radius: 6px; font-size: 13.5px; margin: 12px 0; }
  .staleness.fresh { background: #e8f5ee; border: 1px solid #b9dec8; color: #0a5f3f; }
  .staleness.warn { background: #fcf3e7; border: 1px solid #ecd97a; color: #7a4e00; }
  .staleness.critical { background: #fcebeb; border: 1px solid #e8b9b9; color: #8a1414; }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="wrap">

<header>
  <h1>{{ title }}</h1>
  <div class="meta">
    Generated {{ generated_on }} by <code>energy-moneysaver</code> v0.<br>
    {%- if config.household.notes %}{{ config.household.notes }}<br>{% endif %}
    Tariff data last verified: electricity {{ snapshot.last_verified.electricity }},
    gas {{ snapshot.last_verified.gas }}, hikes {{ snapshot.last_verified.hikes }}.
  </div>
</header>

{%- if staleness != "fresh" %}
<div class="staleness {{ staleness }}">
  <strong>{{ staleness | upper }}:</strong>
  Tariff data is more than {{ "120" if staleness == "critical" else "60" }} days
  old. Rates may be out of date — refresh
  <code>tariffs/electricity.yaml</code> and <code>tariffs/gas.yaml</code>
  before relying on the rankings below.
</div>
{%- endif %}

<div class="tldr">
  <h2>TL;DR</h2>
  <p style="margin:0 0 10px">Top two switching options, ranked by annual cost
    {%- if can_schedule -%} (Shifted scenario: EV charging moved to the plan's cheapest band){% endif %}:</p>
  <table>
    {%- for r in top_two %}
    <tr>
      <td><strong>{{ r.combo.label }}</strong>
        {%- if r.combo.elec.supplier %} — {{ r.combo.elec.supplier }}{% endif %}</td>
      <td class="num"><span class="big-num">€{{ '{:,.0f}'.format(r.cost_shifted_eur) }}</span></td>
    </tr>
    {%- endfor %}
  </table>
  {%- if do_nothing %}
  <p>vs <strong>DO-NOTHING</strong> (€{{ '{:,.0f}'.format(do_nothing.cost_now_eur) }})
    you save up to <strong>€{{ '{:,.0f}'.format(do_nothing.cost_now_eur - top_two[0].cost_shifted_eur) }}/year</strong>.
  </p>
  {%- endif %}
  {%- if baseline and baseline.combo.elec.id != do_nothing.combo.elec.id|default('') %}
  <p>Your current plan (BASELINE, while discount still applies):
    €{{ '{:,.0f}'.format(baseline.cost_now_eur) }}/year.
    {%- if config.electricity.current_plan.discount_expires_on %}
    Discount expires {{ config.electricity.current_plan.discount_expires_on }} — after that
    you would auto-roll onto the post-hike standard plan above unless you switch.
    {%- endif %}
  </p>
  {%- endif %}
</div>

<h2>Full Ranking</h2>
<p class="meta">
  {{ '{:,.0f}'.format(config.electricity.annual_kwh) }} kWh electricity
  {%- if config.gas %} + {{ '{:,.0f}'.format(config.gas.annual_kwh) }} kWh gas{% endif %}
  per year. Baseload pattern: {{ baseload_source }}.
  {%- if can_schedule %}
  "Now" = your current charging habits (default sample distribution).
  "Shifted" = Tesla/EV moved to each plan's cheapest band.
  {%- endif %}
</p>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Rank</th><th>Plan</th><th class="num">Now €</th><th class="num">Shifted €</th><th>Source</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
  {%- set ns = namespace(rank=1) %}
  {%- for r in switchable_results %}
    {%- if loop.index == 1 %}
      {%- set cls = "winner" %}
    {%- elif loop.index == 2 %}
      {%- set cls = "silver" %}
    {%- else %}
      {%- set cls = "" %}
    {%- endif %}
    <tr class="{{ cls }}">
      <td>
        {%- if loop.index == 1 %}🥇 1
        {%- elif loop.index == 2 %}🥈 2
        {%- elif loop.index == 3 %}🥉 3
        {%- else %}{{ loop.index }}
        {%- endif %}
      </td>
      <td><strong>{{ r.combo.label }}</strong>
        <span class="meta">— {{ r.combo.elec.supplier }}</span></td>
      <td class="num">{{ '{:,.0f}'.format(r.cost_now_eur) }}</td>
      <td class="num"><strong>{{ '{:,.0f}'.format(r.cost_shifted_eur) }}</strong></td>
      <td><span class="pill {{ {'FACT':'win','BONKERS':'muted','THIRD_PARTY':'warn','PRESS':'muted'}.get(r.combo.elec.source.confidence, 'muted') }}">{{ r.combo.elec.source.confidence }}</span></td>
    </tr>
  {%- endfor %}
  {%- if baseline %}
    <tr class="baseline">
      <td>—</td>
      <td>{{ baseline.combo.label }}</td>
      <td class="num">{{ '{:,.0f}'.format(baseline.cost_now_eur) }}</td>
      <td class="num">{{ '{:,.0f}'.format(baseline.cost_shifted_eur) }}</td>
      <td>—</td>
    </tr>
  {%- endif %}
  {%- if do_nothing %}
    <tr class="danger">
      <td>🚨</td>
      <td><strong>{{ do_nothing.combo.label }}</strong></td>
      <td class="num"><strong>{{ '{:,.0f}'.format(do_nothing.cost_now_eur) }}</strong></td>
      <td class="num">{{ '{:,.0f}'.format(do_nothing.cost_shifted_eur) }}</td>
      <td>—</td>
    </tr>
  {%- endif %}
  </tbody>
</table>

{%- if hikes %}
<h2>Announced Price Hikes</h2>
<p class="meta">Source: <code>tariffs/hikes.yaml</code> ({{ snapshot.last_verified.hikes }}).</p>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Supplier</th><th class="num">Electricity</th><th class="num">Gas</th><th>Effective</th><th>Announced</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
  {%- for h in hikes %}
    <tr>
      <td>{{ h.supplier }}</td>
      <td class="num">+{{ h.electricity_pct }}%</td>
      <td class="num">+{{ h.gas_pct }}%</td>
      <td>{{ h.effective_date }}</td>
      <td>{{ h.announced_on }}</td>
    </tr>
  {%- endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
{%- endif %}

<h2>Methodology</h2>
<details open>
  <summary>How costs are calculated</summary>
  <ul>
    <li>All rates inc 9% residential VAT, with PSO levy (€{{ '{:.2f}'.format(pso_levy_annual) }}/year inc VAT) and gas carbon tax (€{{ '{:.4f}'.format(gas_carbon_tax_inc_vat) }}/kWh inc VAT) added separately.</li>
    <li>Peak time-of-use rate (17:00–19:00) applies Mon–Fri only — weekend 17–19 hours are charged at Day rate per CRU rules.</li>
    <li>Hourly consumption pattern: {{ baseload_source }}.</li>
    {%- if can_schedule %}
    <li>"Now" column: EV charging spread across hours per a sample unscheduled distribution. "Shifted": all EV kWh moved to the plan's cheapest band (e.g. 02:00-05:00 super-off-peak).</li>
    {%- endif %}
    <li>Welcome credits and free-day discounts deducted from annual total.</li>
    <li>"BASELINE" row uses your current plan's discounted rate (still in effect). "DO-NOTHING" uses the post-discount-expiry standard rate for the same supplier, including any announced hikes.</li>
  </ul>
</details>

<details>
  <summary>Data confidence levels (in source column)</summary>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>FACT</strong> — rate read directly from supplier official page or customer quote.</li>
    <li><strong>BONKERS</strong> — rate from bonkers.ie plan detail page (sources from supplier).</li>
    <li><strong>THIRD_PARTY</strong> — from selectra.ie / saveonheat.ie etc. Usually reliable, second-hand.</li>
    <li><strong>PRESS</strong> — from press coverage (e.g. hike announcements).</li>
    <li><strong>GUESS</strong> — estimated; flagged in plan notes.</li>
  </ul>
</details>

<footer>
  Built with <a href="https://github.com/sophiezhen/energy-moneysaver">energy-moneysaver</a> (MIT).
  All rates are point-in-time snapshots; verify the source URL in <code>tariffs/electricity.yaml</code> / <code>tariffs/gas.yaml</code> before switching.
</footer>

</div>
</body>
</html>
